    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix UE tracer set_current_ue() not updating internal UE state\n\n### Summary\nThe `set_current_ue()` function in the UE tracer was not properly updating the internal UE state tracking. This caused the tracer to display incorrect UE-specific information and not respond to UE selection changes.\n\nThe issue was that while the function updated the UI labels and plot titles, it failed to store the selected UE ID in the `ue_data` structure. This meant subsequent operations would still use the old UE ID.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/utils/T/tracer/ue.c`: \n  - Added UE ID tracking variables and `reset_ue_ids()` function\n  - Modified `set_current_ue()` to properly store the UE ID in the data structure\n  - Added UI elements for UE selection (prev/next/current buttons)\n  - Added click handlers for UE selection\n  - Added initialization of UE tracking in main function\n\n"
}